The paper deals with kernelization algorithms for packing problems in hypergraphs and graphs, which are fundamental topics in computer science. The use of hypergraphs suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as likely categories. The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered by cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GT (Discrete Mathematics).
